A train company has announced plans to expand services, including a town's new and only direct connection to London.Grand Central has applied to the Office of Rail and Road to start consultations on new routes which, if approved, could be launched from May next year.These include the introduction of four daily services from Seaham to London.Also planned are increased services from West Yorkshire to London and additional stops at Peterborough.
The proposals would provide over 360,000 additional seats per year on West Yorkshire services and an additional 195,000 seats annually on the North East route, Grand Central said.
